The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning-based model for automated immunohistochemical scoring, which involves image analysis and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The model also involves sequential learning and policy-based decision-making, which suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of recurrent and residual convolution networks, which are common in natural language processing and text classification, indicating the possibility of cs.CL (Computation and Language) being a relevant category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for reducing the computational burden of analyzing large histology images, which could involve information retrieval and search algorithms, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
